   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>God's Judgment</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The overcomers will succeed, but the majority of the saints will be defeated.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Eventually, God's judgment will be applied to all the believers at the judgment seat of Christ 2 Cor 5:10 . a. The Reward of the Full Enjoyment of Christ in the Kingdom</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God will reward the overcomers with the full enjoyment of Christ in the kingdom.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Today if you are overcoming, you are enjoying Christ, but not in full.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The full enjoyment of Christ will be in the next age.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To participate in the full enjoyment of Christ in the millennial kingdom will be a reward to you.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>1 To Reign with Christ in His Glory</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The full enjoyment of Christ includes being Christ's co-kings in His glory 2 Tim 2:12a; Rev 20:4, 6 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>2 To Partake of the Joy of Christ in His Kingdom</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The glory of Christ and the joy of Christ are the two main items of God's reward to the overcoming saints.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The reigning is in His glory and the joy is in His kingdom.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Matthew 25:21 and 23 reveal that the overcomers will partake of the joy of Christ in His kingdom. b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The Salvation of the Soul from Losing Christ in the Age of Righteousness</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Another aspect of the reward for the overcomers is the salvation of the soul.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>If you have overcome, the Lord will save you from losing Christ in the age of righteousness.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>1 To Be Saved from Being Cast Out into Darkness in the Age of Discipline</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The overcomers will be saved from being cast out into outer darkness in the age of discipline Matt 25:30 .</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Those who do not overcome in this age will lose Christ in the age of righteousness, the age of the kingdom, the age of discipline.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>2 To Be Saved from Being Cut Off from the Full Enjoyment of Christ in His Glory</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Matthew 24:51a says that the defeated ones will be cut asunder.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>That means they will be cut off from Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>When we were saved, we were joined to Christ as one.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>This union with Christ is for our enjoyment of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>But if we are defeated in this age, at the coming back of the Lord, He will cut us asunder, cut us off, from the enjoyment of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Even today if we are defeated, we are in darkness and are cut off from the enjoyment of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>John 15 says that the branches which do not bear fruit are cut off by the Father vv.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>2a, 6 .</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>To cut them off does not mean that they will perish but that they will be cut asunder from the enjoyment of Christ even today.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>If we are such defeated ones, surely at the Lord's coming back, we will be cast out into outer darkness and cut asunder from the very enjoyable Christ in the millennium.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>II.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>TO CONSUMMATE THE NEW JERUSALEM FOR THE FULFILLMENT OF GOD'S DESIRE</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>God's move on the earth through the overcomers is to consummate, to complete, the building of the New Jerusalem for the fulfillment of God's desire.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Today we are in the age of the overcomers.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>In the church life, we must be vital to overcome everything of today's degradation among the Christians.</S>
   </TEXT>
